<body>
    <h1>Structured programming language</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>data types, operators, expressions, control structures;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Functions and program structure: parameter passing conventions, scope ru=
les and storage classes, recursion;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Header files;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Preprocessor;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Pointers and arrays;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Strings;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Multidimensional array;</p></li>
<li>
<p>User defined data types: structures, unions, enumerations;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Input and Output: standard input and output, formatted input and output,=
 file access;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Variable length argument list;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Command line parameters;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Error Handling;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Graphics;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Linking;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Library functions</p></li>
</ol>
<p></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>data types, operators, expressions, control structures;</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Sure =F0=9F=91=8D =E2=80=94 let=E2=80=99s briefly go through each topic =
one by one. These are <strong>core concepts</strong> of any programming lan=
guage (like C, C++, Java, or Python).</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A91.DataTypes">=F0=9F=A7=
=A9 1. <strong>Data Types</strong></h2>
<p>Data types define <strong>what kind of data</strong> a variable can hold=
.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"1e=
f89012-f5df-4cfb-a3f4-5746fb6f6348" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Type</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>int</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>int age =3D 25;</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Stores whole numbers (no decimals)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>float / double</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>float price =3D 10.5;</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Stores numbers with decimals</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>char</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>char grade =3D 'A';</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Stores a single character</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>string</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>"Hello"</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Stores a sequence of characters (text)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>bool</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>true / false</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Logical value (used in conditions)</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int mar=
ks =3D 85;
float temp =3D 36.5;
char letter =3D 'A';
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=E2=9A=99=EF=B8=8F2.Operators">=E2=
=9A=99=EF=B8=8F 2. <strong>Operators</strong></h2>
<p>Operators perform <strong>operations</strong> on variables and values.</=
p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"00=
b67df1-705e-46a2-8028-f5e307cdf175" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Type</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Meaning</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Arithmetic</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>+</code>, <code>-</code>, <code>*</code>, <code>/</code>, <code>%<=
/code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Math operations</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Relational</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;</code>, <code>&gt;=3D</code>, <code>&lt;=
=3D</code>, <code>=3D=3D</code>, <code>!=3D</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Compare two values</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Logical</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>&amp;&amp;</code>, `</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Assignment</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>=3D</code>, <code>+=3D</code>, <code>-=3D</code>, <code>*=3D</code=
>, <code>/=3D</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Assign values</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Increment/Decrement</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>++</code>, <code>--</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Increase or decrease by 1</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int a =
=3D 10, b =3D 5;
int sum =3D a + b;        // Arithmetic
bool check =3D (a &gt; b);   // Relational
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=AE3.Expressions">=F0=9F=
=A7=AE 3. <strong>Expressions</strong></h2>
<p>An expression is <strong>a combination of variables, constants, and oper=
ators</strong> that produces a value.</p>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int res=
ult =3D (a + b) * c - 10;
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Here, <code>(a + b) * c - 10</code> is an <strong>expression</strong> =
=E2=80=94 it calculates a value and assigns it to <code>result</code>.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=814.ControlStructures">=
=F0=9F=94=81 4. <strong>Control Structures</strong></h2>
<p>Control structures <strong>control the flow</strong> of the program =E2=
=80=94 decide <em>what executes and when</em>.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-(a)DecisionMaking">(a) <strong>Deci=
sion Making</strong></h3>
<p>Used for conditional execution.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">if (mar=
ks &gt;=3D 40)
    printf("Pass");
else
    printf("Fail");
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Other types:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>if...else</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>else if</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>switch...case</code></p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-(b)Loops">(b) <strong>Loops</strong=
></h3>
<p>Used for <strong>repeating tasks</strong>.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"5a=
3eaa30-8fd3-479f-a8fa-f4ad4de59e91" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Loop Type</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Purpose</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>for</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>for(i=3D0;i&lt;5;i++)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Known number of repetitions</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>while</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>while(i&lt;5)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Unknown repetitions</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>do...while</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Executes at least once</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">for (in=
t i =3D 1; i &lt;=3D 5; i++) {
    printf("%d ", i);
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-(c)JumpStatements">(c) <strong>Jump=
 Statements</strong></h3>
<p>Used to <strong>change flow suddenly</strong>.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>break</code> =E2=86=92 exit from loop/switch</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>continue</code> =E2=86=92 skip current iteration</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>return</code> =E2=86=92 exit from function</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>In short:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Data types</strong> =E2=86=92 what kind of data</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Operators</strong> =E2=86=92 how to process data</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Expressions</strong> =E2=86=92 combination of data + operators</=
p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Control structures</strong> =E2=86=92 how the program decides an=
d repeats actions</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<p>Would you like me to give <strong>short MCQs and answers</strong> for th=
ese topics (for govt job exam style)?</p>
<ol start=3D"2">
<li>
<p>Functions and program structure: parameter passing conventions, scope ru=
les and storage classes, recursion;</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Excellent =F0=9F=91=8F =E2=80=94 this topic is <strong>core programming =
theory</strong>, and it=E2=80=99s very common in <strong>govt IT exams, =
 ICT</strong>, and <strong>computer fundamentals tests</strong>.</p>
<p>Let=E2=80=99s go through each part clearly and simply =E2=80=94 with sho=
rt examples =F0=9F=91=87</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A91.FunctionsandProgramSt=
ructure">=F0=9F=A7=A9 <strong>1. Functions and Program Structure</strong></=
h2>
<p>A <strong>function</strong> is a <strong>block of code</strong> that per=
forms a specific task.<br>
It helps in reusing code, improving readability, and modular programming.</=
p>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9FunctionSyntax(inC/C++)=
:">=F0=9F=94=B9 Function Syntax (in C/C++):</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">returnT=
ype functionName(parameter list) {
    // body
    return value;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Example:">Example:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int add=
(int a, int b) {
    return a + b;
}

int main() {
    int result =3D add(5, 3);
    printf("%d", result);
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=9F=A2 Output: <code>8</code></p>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=B1ProgramStructure">=F0=
=9F=A7=B1 Program Structure</h3>
<p>A simple C program has:</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Preprocessor directives</strong> =E2=86=92 <code>#include &lt;st=
dio.h&gt;</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Global declarations</strong> =E2=86=92 global variables or const=
ants</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Functions</strong> =E2=86=92 <code>main()</code> and user-define=
d ones</p></li>
</ol>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 Example structure:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int square(int x); // function declaration

int main() {
    int num =3D 4;
    printf("%d", square(num));
    return 0;
}

int square(int x) {  // function definition
    return x * x;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=E2=9A=99=EF=B8=8F2.ParameterPassin=
gConventions">=E2=9A=99=EF=B8=8F <strong>2. Parameter Passing Conventions</=
strong></h2>
<p>When we call a function, we can <strong>pass data (arguments)</strong> i=
n two main ways:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"99=
e98609-8ba9-4bca-a7b3-77d3bea3459f" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Type</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Meaning</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Behavior</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Call by Value</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>A <strong>copy</strong> of the variable is sent</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>add(x, y)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Changes inside function <strong>don=E2=80=99t affect</strong> original v=
ariables</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Call by Reference</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>The <strong>actual variable address</strong> is sent</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>add(&amp;x, &amp;y)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Changes inside function <strong>affect</strong> original variables</p></=
td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Example:.1">Example:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">// Call=
 by value
void modify(int a) {
    a =3D a + 5;
}

int main() {
    int x =3D 10;
    modify(x);
    printf("%d", x); // Output: 10 (no change)
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A03.ScopeRules">=F0=9F=A7=
=A0 <strong>3. Scope Rules</strong></h2>
<p>Scope means <strong>where a variable can be accessed</strong>.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"df=
fff3c2-09fc-41d6-9dd0-8b994be8ddb9" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Type</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Description</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Local Scope</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Declared inside a function/block =E2=80=94 accessible only there</p></td=
>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>int x</code> inside main()</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Global Scope</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Declared outside all functions =E2=80=94 accessible anywhere</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>int x</code> outside main()</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Block Scope</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Declared inside <code>{ }</code> =E2=80=94 exists only within that block=
</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>for (int i=3D0; i&lt;5; i++)</code></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int g =
=3D 100; // global

void show() {
    int x =3D 5; // local
    printf("%d", x);
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=97=82=EF=B8=8F4.StorageClass=
es">=F0=9F=97=82=EF=B8=8F <strong>4. Storage Classes</strong></h2>
<p>Storage classes define <strong>how long</strong>, <strong>where</strong>=
, and <strong>how accessible</strong> a variable is.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"a2=
37e820-a669-4fa1-849a-e56b1d342810" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Keyword</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Scope</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Lifetime</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Default Value</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Meaning</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>auto</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Local</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Function/block</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Garbage</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Default for local variables</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>static</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Local/Global</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Program lifetime</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>0</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Keeps value between function calls</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>extern</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Global</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Program lifetime</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>0</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Declared in another file or outside function</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>register</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Local</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Function/block</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Garbage</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Stored in CPU register (faster access)</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">void co=
unter() {
    static int count =3D 0;
    count++;
    printf("%d ", count);
}

int main() {
    counter(); // 1
    counter(); // 2
    counter(); // 3
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=9F=A2 <em>Static variable keeps its value between calls.</em></p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=815.Recursion">=F0=9F=94=
=81 <strong>5. Recursion</strong></h2>
<p>Recursion means a <strong>function calling itself</strong> directly or i=
ndirectly.</p>
<p>It=E2=80=99s used when a problem can be divided into <strong>smaller sub=
problems</strong> of the same type.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Example:Factorialusingrecursion">Ex=
ample: Factorial using recursion</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int fac=
torial(int n) {
    if (n =3D=3D 1)
        return 1;          // base case
    else
        return n * factorial(n - 1);  // recursive call
}

int main() {
    printf("%d", factorial(5));
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=9F=A2 Output: <code>120</code><br>
=F0=9F=93=9D Here, <code>factorial(5)</code> =E2=86=92 <code>5 * 4 * 3 * 2 =
* 1</code>.</p>
<hr>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>Summary Table</strong></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"4a=
2c6e19-b841-405c-8b4c-72966d024f8a" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Concept</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Function</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Block of reusable code</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Parameter Passing</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Sending data to function (by value/reference)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Scope</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Where variable is visible</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Storage Class</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>How long variable exists &amp; where stored</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Recursion</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Function calling itself</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
