<ol start=3D"3">
<li>
<p>Header files;</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Excellent =F0=9F=91=8D =E2=80=94 understanding <strong>header files</str=
ong> is very important, especially for <strong>C/C++</strong> and <strong>G=
ovt IT job /  ICT</strong> exams.<br>
Let=E2=80=99s explain it <strong>simply and clearly</strong> =F0=9F=91=87</=
p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A9WhatisaHeaderFile?">=F0=
=9F=A7=A9 <strong>What is a Header File?</strong></h2>
<p>A <strong>header file</strong> is a file that contains <strong>function =
declarations</strong>, <strong>macros</strong>, <strong>constants</strong>,=
 and sometimes <strong>data type definitions</strong> that can be used by m=
any C programs.</p>
<p>You include it at the beginning of your program using the <code>#include=
</code> directive.</p>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A0PurposeofHeaderFiles">=
=F0=9F=A7=A0 <strong>Purpose of Header Files</strong></h3>
<p>=E2=9C=85 To reuse commonly used functions<br>
=E2=9C=85 To make code modular and organized<br>
=E2=9C=85 To avoid rewriting function declarations<br>
=E2=9C=85 To use predefined library functions (like <code>printf()</code>, =
<code>scanf()</code>, etc.)</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=BEHowtoIncludeHeaderFiles=
">=F0=9F=A7=BE <strong>How to Include Header Files</strong></h2>
<p>There are two types of includes:</p>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B91.StandardLibraryHeader=
Files">=F0=9F=94=B9 1. <strong>Standard Library Header Files</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>These come with the C/C++ compiler.</p></li>
<li>
<p>They are enclosed in <strong>angle brackets </strong><code>&lt; &gt;</co=
de>.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;   // standard input-output
#include &lt;math.h&gt;    // math functions
#include &lt;string.h&gt;  // string operations
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=9F=A2 Example program:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;
#include &lt;math.h&gt;

int main() {
    printf("Square root of 16 is %.2f", sqrt(16));
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B92.User-DefinedHeaderFil=
es">=F0=9F=94=B9 2. <strong>User-Defined Header Files</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Created by the programmer.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Used to share your own functions across multiple files.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Enclosed in <strong>double quotes </strong><code>" "</code>.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e "myheader.h"
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Suppose you create:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">// myhe=
ader.h
void greet() {
    printf("Hello, User!");
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>and then in main file:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;
#include "myheader.h"

int main() {
    greet();
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=9F=A2 Output: <code>Hello, User!</code></p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=93=9ACommonStandardHeaderFil=
esinC">=F0=9F=93=9A <strong>Common Standard Header Files in C</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"ef=
725cd1-9431-4cc8-894d-7e9c57b90dc9" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
