</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=E2=9A=99=EF=B8=8FHowHeaderFilesWor=
kInternally">=E2=9A=99=EF=B8=8F <strong>How Header Files Work Internally</s=
trong></h2>
<p>When you write:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=91=89 the <strong>preprocessor</strong> literally copies the cont=
ents of that header file into your program <strong>before compilation</stro=
ng>.</p>
<p>It=E2=80=99s as if the file=E2=80=99s contents are pasted at that line.<=
/p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A0InShort">=F0=9F=A7=A0 <=
strong>In Short</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"1d=
34a410-c6b9-43f4-b8b5-b98297f2f540" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Concept</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Explanation</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Header File</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>File that contains function declarations and macros</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Include Syntax</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#include &lt;filename&gt;</code> or <code>#include "filename"</cod=
e></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Types</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Standard library &amp; User-defined</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>Purpose</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Reuse code, use library functions, organize program</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
