<p>Would you like me to give you <strong>MCQs (two-column format)</strong> =
on header files next =E2=80=94 just like before?</p>
<ol start=3D"4">
<li>
<p>Preprocessor;</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Excellent =F0=9F=91=8F =E2=80=94 the <strong>C Preprocessor</strong> is =
one of the most <strong>important but often overlooked</strong> topics in I=
CT/government IT exams.<br>
Let=E2=80=99s understand it <strong>clearly, step by step</strong>, with ex=
amples =F0=9F=91=87</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A9WhatisaPreprocessor?">=
=F0=9F=A7=A9 <strong>What is a Preprocessor?</strong></h2>
<p>Before a C program is compiled, it first passes through a <strong>Prepro=
cessor</strong>.</p>
<p>=F0=9F=A7=A0 The <strong>preprocessor</strong> performs <strong>text sub=
stitution and file inclusion</strong> <em>before actual compilation starts.=
</em></p>
<p>It handles all lines starting with <code>#</code> (hash symbol).</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=E2=9A=99=EF=B8=8FRoleofthePreproce=
ssor">=E2=9A=99=EF=B8=8F <strong>Role of the Preprocessor</strong></h2>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Includes header files<br>
=E2=9C=85 Defines constants and macros<br>
=E2=9C=85 Controls conditional compilation<br>
=E2=9C=85 Replaces macros and removes comments</p>
<p>After preprocessing, the <strong>compiler</strong> receives the expanded=
 source code.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A0MainPreprocessorDirecti=
ves">=F0=9F=A7=A0 <strong>Main Preprocessor Directives</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"f7=
6475fc-679f-4f0b-81d2-21d02e09c007" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Directive</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Purpose</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#include</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Includes header files</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#define</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Defines constants or macros</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#undef</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Undefines a macro</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#ifdef</code> / <code>#ifndef</code> / <code>#if</code> / <code>#e=
lse</code> / <code>#endif</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Conditional compilation</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#error</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Generates an error message during compilation</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#pragma</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Gives special instructions to the compiler</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B91.#include">=F0=9F=94=
=B9 1. <code>#include</code></h3>
<p>Used to include a header file.</p>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>Example:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;
#include "myheader.h"
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=93=98 <code>&lt; &gt;</code><em> for system files, </em><code>" "=
</code><em> for user-defined files.</em></p>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B92.#define=E2=80=94Macro=
Definition">=F0=9F=94=B9 2. <code>#define</code> =E2=80=94 <strong>Macro De=
finition</strong></h3>
<p>Used to define constants or short code replacements.</p>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>Example 1:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#define=
 PI 3.1416

float area =3D PI * r * r;
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>Example 2 (macro function):</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#define=
 SQUARE(x) (x * x)

int a =3D SQUARE(5);   // expands to (5 * 5)
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 <em>The preprocessor replaces every occurrence of </em><cod=
e>PI</code><em> or </em><code>SQUARE(x)</code><em> before compilation.</em>=
</p>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B93.#undef">=F0=9F=94=B9 =
3. <code>#undef</code></h3>
<p>Used to <strong>cancel</strong> a previous <code>#define</code>.</p>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#define=
 SIZE 100
#undef SIZE
#define SIZE 200
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B94.ConditionalCompilatio=
n">=F0=9F=94=B9 4. <strong>Conditional Compilation</strong></h3>
<p>Used to compile specific parts of code depending on conditions.</p>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#define=
 DEBUG 1

#ifdef DEBUG
    printf("Debug mode ON\n");
#endif
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 <em>If </em><code>DEBUG</code><em> is defined, that block w=
ill compile.</em></p>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B95.#if,#else,#elif,#endi=
f">=F0=9F=94=B9 5. <code>#if</code>, <code>#else</code>, <code>#elif</code>=
, <code>#endif</code></h3>
<p>Used for advanced conditional compilation.</p>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#define=
 VERSION 2

#if VERSION =3D=3D 1
    printf("Old version\n");
#elif VERSION =3D=3D 2
    printf("New version\n");
#else
    printf("Unknown version\n");
#endif
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B96.#pragma">=F0=9F=94=B9=
 6. <code>#pragma</code></h3>
<p>Used to give special commands to the compiler.</p>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#pragma=
 startup init
#pragma exit cleanup
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 These tell the compiler to call <code>init()</code> before =
<code>main()</code> and <code>cleanup()</code> after <code>main()</code> (d=
epends on compiler).</p>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B97.#error">=F0=9F=94=B9 =
7. <code>#error</code></h3>
<p>Used to stop compilation and display a custom error.</p>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#if VER=
SION &lt; 2
#error "Version too old!"
#endif
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=81OrderofCompilationSteps=
">=F0=9F=94=81 <strong>Order of Compilation Steps</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Source =
Code (.c)
      =E2=86=93
Preprocessor (# directives handled)
      =E2=86=93
Expanded Source
      =E2=86=93
Compiler (converts to object code)
      =E2=86=93
Linker (links libraries)
      =E2=86=93
Executable (.exe)
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=93=9AQuickSummaryTable">=F0=
=9F=93=9A <strong>Quick Summary Table</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"a5=
7696be-5ee3-4862-94c9-a023691a2034" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Directive</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Meaning</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#include</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Include header file</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#define</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Define macro/constant</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#define PI 3.14</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#undef</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Remove macro definition</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#undef PI</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#ifdef</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>If defined</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#ifdef DEBUG</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#ifndef</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>If not defined</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#ifndef TEST</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#if / #elif / #else / #endif</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Conditional compilation</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#if VALUE =3D=3D 10</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#error</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Generate compile-time error</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#error "Invalid Input"</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#pragma</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Compiler-specific instruction</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>#pragma once</code></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>In Short:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>The <strong>C Preprocessor</strong> prepares your code before compilatio=
n =E2=80=94 it <strong>includes files, replaces macros, and controls which =
code gets compiled.</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p>Would you like me to give a <strong>two-column MCQ set</strong> on <em>P=
reprocessor directives</em> next (exam-style, like before)?</p>
<ol start=3D"5">
<li>
<p>Pointers and arrays;</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Excellent =F0=9F=91=8F =E2=80=94 =E2=80=9C<strong>Pointers and Arrays</s=
trong>=E2=80=9D is one of the <strong>most important &amp; confusing</stron=
g> chapters in C programming =E2=80=94 but once you understand the relation=
ship between them, everything becomes very logical and easy.</p>
<p>Let=E2=80=99s go step-by-step clearly =F0=9F=91=87</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A9WhatisaPointer?">=F0=9F=
=A7=A9 <strong>What is a Pointer?</strong></h2>
<p>=F0=9F=91=89 A <strong>pointer</strong> is a <strong>variable that store=
s the memory address</strong> of another variable.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Example:.2">Example:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int a =
=3D 10;
int *p;      // declare pointer
p =3D &amp;a;      // assign address of a to pointer p
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=A7=A0 <strong>Explanation:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>a</code> holds the value <code>10</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>&amp;a</code> gives the <strong>address of a</strong></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>p</code> holds that address</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>*p</code> gives the <strong>value stored at that address</strong><=
/p></li>
</ul>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">printf(=
"%d", *p);   // prints 10
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=93=A6MemoryConcept">=F0=9F=
=93=A6 <strong>Memory Concept</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"95=
95dec6-e025-40b6-a88f-1ad0225de069" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Variable</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Value</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Address (example)</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>a</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>10</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>1000</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>p</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>1000</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>2000</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=91=89 <code>p</code> =E2=86=92 points to =E2=86=92 <code>a</code>=
</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A0PointerOperators">=F0=
=9F=A7=A0 <strong>Pointer Operators</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"38=
e0bc3d-b051-4569-9f43-22f21447ca0f" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Operator</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Meaning</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>&amp;</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Address-of operator</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>*</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Value-at (dereference) operator</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int x =
=3D 5;
int *ptr =3D &amp;x;
printf("%d", *ptr); // 5
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9PointertoPointer">=F0=
=9F=94=B9 <strong>Pointer to Pointer</strong></h2>
<p>You can have a pointer that stores the address of another pointer.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int a =
=3D 10;
int *p =3D &amp;a;
int **q =3D &amp;p;

printf("%d", **q); // prints 10
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=B1WhatisanArray?">=F0=9F=
=A7=B1 <strong>What is an Array?</strong></h2>
<p>=F0=9F=91=89 An <strong>array</strong> is a <strong>collection of elemen=
ts</strong> of the same type stored in <strong>contiguous memory</strong>.<=
/p>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int arr=
[3] =3D {10, 20, 30};
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=A7=A0 Memory layout:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"a8=
570d86-adfe-4bce-8b88-274891c9b0c5" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Index</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Address</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Value</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>0</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>1000</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>10</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>1</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>1004</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>20</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>1008</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>30</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>(assuming each int =3D 4 bytes)</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=92=A1RelationshipBetweenArra=
ysandPointers">=F0=9F=92=A1 <strong>Relationship Between Arrays and Pointer=
s</strong></h2>
<p>=F0=9F=91=89 The <strong>array name itself acts like a pointer</strong> =
to its first element.</p>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int arr=
[3] =3D {10, 20, 30};
printf("%d", *arr);      // prints 10
printf("%d", *(arr + 1)); // prints 20
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=92=AC Here:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>arr</code> =3D address of <code>arr[0]</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>arr + 1</code> =3D address of <code>arr[1]</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>*(arr + 1)</code> =3D value at that address =E2=86=92 <code>20</co=
de></p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9PointerArithmetic">=F0=
=9F=94=B9 Pointer Arithmetic</h3>
<p>You can move through an array using pointer arithmetic.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int arr=
[3] =3D {10, 20, 30};
int *p =3D arr;

printf("%d\n", *p);     // 10
p++;
printf("%d\n", *p);     // 20
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=93=98 When you increment a pointer, it moves to the <strong>next =
element=E2=80=99s address</strong> (not +1 byte, but +sizeof(type)).</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=81ArrayTraversalUsingPoin=
ters">=F0=9F=94=81 <strong>Array Traversal Using Pointers</strong></h2>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int arr=
[] =3D {10, 20, 30, 40, 50};
int *p =3D arr;

for(int i =3D 0; i &lt; 5; i++) {
    printf("%d ", *(p + i));
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Output:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">10 20 3=
0 40 50
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A0ImportantFacts">=F0=9F=
=A7=A0 <strong>Important Facts</strong></h2>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><code>arr</code> and <code>&amp;arr[0]</code> =E2=86=92 same address</p>=
</li>
<li>
<p>But <code>arr</code> and <code>&amp;arr</code> have <strong>different ty=
pes</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>arr</code> =E2=86=92 pointer to first element</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>&amp;arr</code> =E2=86=92 pointer to the entire array</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><code>*(arr + i)</code> is same as <code>arr[i]</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>Pointer arithmetic depends on the data type.</p></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9PointerandArrayExamplew=
ithStrings">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>Pointer and Array Example with Strings</st=
rong></h2>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">char na=
me[] =3D "Ruhul";
char *p =3D name;

while(*p !=3D '\0') {
    printf("%c", *p);
    p++;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Output:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Ruhul
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=E2=9A=99=EF=B8=8FPointerstoArraysv=
sArrayofPointers">=E2=9A=99=EF=B8=8F <strong>Pointers to Arrays vs Array of=
 Pointers</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"7a=
e00412-8e73-423e-9839-632ef29d5774" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Concept</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Description</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Pointer to array</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>One pointer pointing to an entire array</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>int (*p)[5];</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Array of pointers</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Multiple pointers stored in an array</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>int *p[5];</code></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=93=9ASummaryTable">=F0=9F=93=
=9A <strong>Summary Table</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"d5=
9442f3-93e6-4e18-aef1-21860a93707e" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Concept</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Meaning</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Declare pointer</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>int *p;</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>p can hold address of int</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Assign address</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>p =3D &amp;a;</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>p stores address of a</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Dereference</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>*p</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Value at address</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Pointer to array</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>int *p =3D arr;</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>p points to arr[0]</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Access using pointer</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>*(p+i)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>same as <code>arr[i]</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Increment pointer</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>p++</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>moves to next element</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>In Short:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<ul>
<li>
<p>A <strong>pointer</strong> holds a <strong>memory address</strong>.</p><=
/li>
<li>
<p>An <strong>array name</strong> is like a <strong>constant pointer</stron=
g>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>You can access array elements using pointers and pointer arithmetic.</p>=
</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p>Would you like me to give you an <strong>MCQ practice set (15 questions)=
</strong> on <em>Pointers &amp; Arrays</em> =E2=80=94 formatted like an ICT=
 exam sheet (with answers and explanations)?</p>
<ol start=3D"6">
<li>
<p>Strings;</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Excellent =F0=9F=91=8F =E2=80=94 now let=E2=80=99s cover <strong>Strings=
</strong> =E2=80=94 one of the most common C programming topics that freque=
ntly appears in <strong>Govt IT /  ICT</strong> exams.</p>
<p>We=E2=80=99ll go step-by-step so you understand it fully =F0=9F=91=87</p=
>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A9WhatisaString?">=F0=9F=
=A7=A9 <strong>What is a String?</strong></h2>
<p>=F0=9F=91=89 A <strong>string</strong> in C is a <strong>sequence of cha=
racters</strong> stored in memory <strong>terminated by a null character (<=
/strong><code>'\0'</code><strong>)</strong>.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Example:.3">Example:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">char na=
me[] =3D "Ruhul";
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=A7=A0 Internally it is stored as:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"c6=
c1d43e-5880-4521-8360-1401ef90050c" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Index</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>0</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>1</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>2</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>3</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>4</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>5</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Value</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>R</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>u</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>h</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>u</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>l</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>\0</code></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <code>\0</code> =3D null character (marks the <strong>end of s=
tring</strong>)</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=B1StringDeclaration">=F0=
=9F=A7=B1 <strong>String Declaration</strong></h2>
<p>There are two main ways to declare strings in C:</p>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B91.CharacterArray">=F0=
=9F=94=B9 1. <strong>Character Array</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">char st=
r[6] =3D {'H','e','l','l','o','\0'};
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B92.StringLiteral(Shortcu=
t)">=F0=9F=94=B9 2. <strong>String Literal (Shortcut)</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">char st=
r[] =3D "Hello";
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 The compiler automatically adds <code>'\0'</code>.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=93=A5StringInputandOutput">=
=F0=9F=93=A5 <strong>String Input and Output</strong></h2>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=E2=9C=85Usingprintf()andscanf()">=
=E2=9C=85 Using <code>printf()</code> and <code>scanf()</code></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">char na=
me[20];
printf("Enter your name: ");
scanf("%s", name);   // input stops at first space
printf("Hello %s", name);
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=E2=9A=A0=EF=B8=8FLimitation:">=E2=
=9A=A0=EF=B8=8F Limitation:</h3>
<p><code>scanf()</code> stops reading at space, tab, or newline.<br>
If you input =E2=80=9CMd Ruhul=E2=80=9D, only =E2=80=9CMd=E2=80=9D will be =
read.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=E2=9C=85Toreadfullline(withspaces)=
:">=E2=9C=85 To read full line (with spaces):</h3>
<p>Use <code>gets()</code> or better, <code>fgets()</code>:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">char na=
me[50];
fgets(name, 50, stdin);
printf("Hello %s", name);
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=A7StringFunctions(from<st=
ring.h>)">=F0=9F=94=A7 <strong>String Functions (from </strong><code>&lt;st=
ring.h&gt;</code><strong>)</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"5b=
cf9bb3-d559-4487-932b-3b97adccfb31" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Function</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Description</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>strlen(str)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Returns length of string (excluding <code>\0</code>)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>strlen("Hi") =E2=86=92 2</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>strcpy(dest, src)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Copies string <code>src</code> to <code>dest</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>strcpy(a, b)</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>strcat(s1, s2)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Concatenates two strings</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>"Hi" + "Bye" =3D "HiBye"</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>strcmp(s1, s2)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Compares two strings</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>0</code> if equal</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>strupr(str)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Converts to uppercase (compiler-specific)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>"abc" =E2=86=92 "ABC"</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>strlwr(str)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Converts to lowercase (compiler-specific)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>"ABC" =E2=86=92 "abc"</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>strrev(str)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Reverses string (compiler-specific)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>"abc" =E2=86=92 "cba"</code></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=92=A1Examples">=F0=9F=92=A1 =
<strong>Examples</strong></h2>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B91.FindStringLength">=F0=
=9F=94=B9 1. <strong>Find String Length</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;
#include &lt;string.h&gt;

int main() {
    char name[] =3D "Ruhul";
    printf("Length: %d", strlen(name));
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output: <code>Length: 5</code></p>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B92.CopyaString">=F0=9F=
=94=B9 2. <strong>Copy a String</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">char sr=
c[] =3D "Govt Job";
char dest[20];
strcpy(dest, src);
printf("%s", dest);
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output: <code>Govt Job</code></p>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B93.CompareTwoStrings">=
=F0=9F=94=B9 3. <strong>Compare Two Strings</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">char a[=
] =3D "Hello";
char b[] =3D "World";

if(strcmp(a,b) =3D=3D 0)
    printf("Equal");
else
    printf("Not Equal");
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output: <code>Not Equal</code></p>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B94.ConcatenateTwoStrings=
">=F0=9F=94=B9 4. <strong>Concatenate Two Strings</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">char s1=
[20] =3D "Govt ";
char s2[] =3D "Job";
strcat(s1, s2);
printf("%s", s1);
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output: <code>Govt Job</code></p>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B95.ManualStringTraversal=
">=F0=9F=94=B9 5. <strong>Manual String Traversal</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">char st=
r[] =3D "Hello";
int i =3D 0;

while(str[i] !=3D '\0') {
    printf("%c ", str[i]);
    i++;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output: <code>H e l l o</code></p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A0HowStringsWorkinMemory"=
>=F0=9F=A7=A0 <strong>How Strings Work in Memory</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Strings are <strong>arrays of characters</strong></p></li>
<li>
<p>Each character takes <strong>1 byte</strong></p></li>
<li>
<p>The last byte is <code>\0</code><strong> (null terminator)</strong></p><=
/li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Example:.4">Example:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">char s[=
] =3D "ICT";
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"0d=
1e1fb4-b08b-47ca-b69a-2451a1d92633" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Index</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>0</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>1</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>2</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>3</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Value</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>I</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>C</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>T</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>\0</code></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=E2=9A=99=EF=B8=8FDifferenceBetween=
CharandString">=E2=9A=99=EF=B8=8F <strong>Difference Between Char and Strin=
g</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"e9=
c12ed8-a504-49d7-90cc-0c80e24dedb6" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Type</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Meaning</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>char c =3D 'A';</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Single character</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>'A'</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>char s[] =3D "A";</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>String (2 chars: 'A' + <code>\0</code>)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>"A\0"</code></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=BEStringvsCharacterArray"=
>=F0=9F=A7=BE <strong>String vs Character Array</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"80=
1d6d5e-ebb4-4c0f-a171-549e7a3c404f" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Concept</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>String</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Character Array</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Declaration</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>char str[] =3D "Hi";</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>char str[3] =3D {'H','i','\0'};</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Size</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Auto-added <code>\0</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Must add <code>\0</code> manually</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Library Support</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>&lt;string.h&gt;</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Manual processing</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Use</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Easier and safer</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Lower-level control</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A0KeyNotes">=F0=9F=A7=A0 =
<strong>Key Notes</strong></h2>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Always ensure your array has space for <code>'\0'</code><br>
=E2=9C=85 <code>str1 =3D=3D str2</code> <strong>does not compare strings</s=
trong> =E2=80=94 use <code>strcmp()</code> instead<br>
=E2=9C=85 String operations require <code>&lt;string.h&gt;</code><br>
=E2=9C=85 Avoid <code>gets()</code> (unsafe); use <code>fgets()</code></p>
