<p>Perfect =F0=9F=91=8F =E2=80=94 now let=E2=80=99s cover <strong>Multidime=
nsional Arrays</strong> in C. This is a <strong>key topic</strong> for prog=
ramming exams like <strong>Govt IT /  ICT</strong>. I=E2=80=99ll explain=
 it <strong>step by step with examples</strong>.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A9WhatisaMultidimensional=
Array?">=F0=9F=A7=A9 <strong>What is a Multidimensional Array?</strong></h2=
>
<p>=F0=9F=91=89 A <strong>multidimensional array</strong> is an <strong>arr=
ay of arrays</strong>.<br>
It allows you to store data in <strong>rows and columns</strong> (like a ta=
ble or matrix).</p>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Syntax:">Syntax:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">data_ty=
pe array_name[size1][size2]...[sizeN];
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>size1, size2,...</code> =E2=86=92 number of elements in each dimen=
sion</p></li>
<li>
<p>Most common: <strong>2D array</strong> (rows =C3=97 columns)</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B91.Two-Dimensional(2D)Ar=
ray">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>1. Two-Dimensional (2D) Array</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Think of it as a <strong>table</strong> with <strong>rows and columns</s=
trong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Example:Declarea2Darray">Example: D=
eclare a 2D array</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int mat=
rix[2][3]; // 2 rows, 3 columns
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Assignvalues">Assign values</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">matrix[=
0][0] =3D 1;
matrix[0][1] =3D 2;
matrix[0][2] =3D 3;
matrix[1][0] =3D 4;
matrix[1][1] =3D 5;
matrix[1][2] =3D 6;
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-MemoryRepresentation">Memory Repres=
entation</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"d2=
e392f2-5bfe-4f7e-97b6-20bfa88c0171" class=3D"confluenceTable">
