<p>Value</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>[0][0]</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>1</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>[0][1]</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>2</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>[0][2]</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>[1][0]</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>4</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>[1][1]</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>5</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>[1][2]</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>6</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B92.InitializationatDecla=
ration">=F0=9F=94=B9 2. Initialization at Declaration</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int mat=
rix[2][3] =3D { {1,2,3}, {4,5,6} };
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>or using <strong>flattened form</strong>:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int mat=
rix[2][3] =3D {1,2,3,4,5,6};
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B93.AccessingElements">=
=F0=9F=94=B9 3. Accessing Elements</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">printf(=
"%d", matrix[1][2]); // prints 6
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B94.Traversinga2DArray">=
=F0=9F=94=B9 4. Traversing a 2D Array</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">for(int=
 i =3D 0; i &lt; 2; i++) {          // rows
    for(int j =3D 0; j &lt; 3; j++) {      // columns
        printf("%d ", matrix[i][j]);
    }
    printf("\n");
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">1 2 3
4 5 6
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B93.Three-Dimensional(3D)=
Array">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>3. Three-Dimensional (3D) Array</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Think of it as a <strong>cube</strong> or <strong>stack of matrices</str=
ong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Declaration:">Declaration:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int arr=
[2][3][4]; // 2 blocks, 3 rows, 4 columns
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Example:.5">Example:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int arr=
[2][2][3] =3D {=20
    { {1,2,3}, {4,5,6} },=20
    { {7,8,9}, {10,11,12} }=20
};
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Access:">Access:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">printf(=
"%d", arr[1][0][2]); // prints 9
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9ImportantNotes">=F0=9F=
=94=B9 <strong>Important Notes</strong></h2>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Row-Major Storage</strong>: In C, multidimensional arrays are st=
ored <strong>row by row</strong> in memory.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Index starts at 0</strong>: First row =E2=86=92 0, first column =
=E2=86=92 0</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Size must be constant</strong> (for standard C arrays)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Can be <strong>partially initialized</strong>: uninitialized elements be=
come 0.</p></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B92DArrayExampleProgram">=
=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>2D Array Example Program</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int main() {
    int matrix[2][3] =3D { {1,2,3}, {4,5,6} };

    printf("Matrix:\n");
    for(int i =3D 0; i &lt; 2; i++) {
        for(int j =3D 0; j &lt; 3; j++) {
            printf("%d ", matrix[i][j]);
        }
        printf("\n");
    }

    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Matrix:
1 2 3
4 5 6
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9QuickSummaryTable">=F0=
=9F=94=B9 <strong>Quick Summary Table</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"b6=
ee4a21-e8c3-4249-a711-d35d34707b8c" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Concept</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Explanation</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>2D Array</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>int a[2][3];</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>2 rows =C3=97 3 columns</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>3D Array</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>int a[2][3][4];</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>2 matrices =C3=97 3 rows =C3=97 4 columns</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Access Element</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>a[1][2]</code></p></td>
