</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Traverse</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Nested loops</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Outer =E2=86=92 rows, Inner =E2=86=92 columns</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Initialization</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>int a[2][3] =3D {{1,2,3},{4,5,6}};</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Directly assign values</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>In Short:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Multidimensional arrays let you store <strong>data in tabular or matrix =
form</strong>, and you can traverse them using <strong>nested loops</strong=
>.<br>
2D arrays =E2=86=92 most common; 3D or higher =E2=86=92 rare, usually for a=
dvanced problems.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p>I can make a <strong>two-column MCQ sheet (15 questions) on Multidimensi=
onal Arrays</strong> next, just like your previous MCQs.</p>
<p>Do you want me to do that?</p>
<ol start=3D"8">
<li>
<p>User defined data types: structures, unions, enumerations;</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Perfect =F0=9F=91=8F =E2=80=94 now let=E2=80=99s cover <strong>User-Defi=
ned Data Types (UDTs)</strong> in C: <strong>Structures, Unions, and Enumer=
ations</strong>. These are very important for <strong>Govt IT /  ICT exa=
ms</strong>. I=E2=80=99ll explain clearly with examples.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A91.Structures(struct)">=
=F0=9F=A7=A9 <strong>1. Structures (</strong><code>struct</code><strong>)</=
strong></h2>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9WhatisaStructure?">=F0=
=9F=94=B9 <strong>What is a Structure?</strong></h3>
<p>A <strong>structure</strong> is a <strong>user-defined data type</strong=
> that can store <strong>different types of data together</strong> under a =
single name.</p>
<p>Think of it as a <strong>record</strong> or <strong>object</strong>.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Syntax:.1">Syntax:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">struct =
structure_name {
    data_type member1;
    data_type member2;
    ...
};
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Example:.6">Example:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;

struct Student {
    int id;
    char name[20];
    float marks;
};

int main() {
    struct Student s1;

    s1.id =3D 101;
    strcpy(s1.name, "Ruhul");
    s1.marks =3D 85.5;

    printf("ID: %d\nName: %s\nMarks: %.2f\n", s1.id, s1.name, s1.marks);
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">ID: 101
Name: Ruhul
Marks: 85.50
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-KeyPoints:">Key Points:</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Can contain <strong>different data types</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Access members using <strong>dot operator (</strong><code>.</code><stron=
g>)</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Useful for <strong>grouping related data</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A92.Unions(union)">=F0=9F=
=A7=A9 <strong>2. Unions (</strong><code>union</code><strong>)</strong></h2=
>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9WhatisaUnion?">=F0=9F=
=94=B9 <strong>What is a Union?</strong></h3>
<p>A <strong>union</strong> is similar to a structure, but <strong>all memb=
ers share the same memory location</strong>.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Only <strong>one member</strong> can store a value at a time.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Saves memory but overwrites previous value if you assign a new member.</=
p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Syntax:.2">Syntax:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">union u=
nion_name {
    data_type member1;
    data_type member2;
    ...
};
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Example:.7">Example:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;

union Data {
    int i;
    float f;
    char str[20];
};

int main() {
    union Data d;

    d.i =3D 10;
    printf("i: %d\n", d.i);

    d.f =3D 3.14;  // overwrites previous i
    printf("f: %.2f\n", d.f);

    strcpy(d.str, "Hello");  // overwrites previous f
    printf("str: %s\n", d.str);

    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">i: 10
f: 3.14
str: Hello
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-KeyPoints:.1">Key Points:</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Saves memory.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Only <strong>one member usable at a time</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Access members using <strong>dot operator (</strong><code>.</code><stron=
g>)</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A93.Enumerations(enum)">=
=F0=9F=A7=A9 <strong>3. Enumerations (</strong><code>enum</code><strong>)</=
strong></h2>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9WhatisanEnumeration?">=
=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>What is an Enumeration?</strong></h3>
<p>An <strong>enumeration</strong> is a user-defined type that consists of =
a set of <strong>named integer constants</strong>.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Useful for <strong>making code readable</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Each name gets an integer value by default, starting from 0.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Syntax:.3">Syntax:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">enum en=
um_name { name1, name2, ..., nameN };
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Example:.8">Example:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;

enum Week { Sunday, Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday =
};

int main() {
    enum Week today;
    today =3D Wednesday;

    printf("Day number: %d\n", today); // Wednesday =3D 3
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Day num=
ber: 3
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-KeyPoints:.2">Key Points:</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Default values start from <strong>0</strong> and increment by 1.</p></li=
>
<li>
<p>Can <strong>assign custom values</strong>:</p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">enum Mo=
nth { Jan=3D1, Feb, Mar, Apr };
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Makes code more <strong>readable and maintainable</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=E2=9A=99=EF=B8=8FComparisonTable:s=
tructvsunionvsenum">=E2=9A=99=EF=B8=8F <strong>Comparison Table: </strong><=
code>struct</code><strong> vs </strong><code>union</code><strong> vs </stro=
ng><code>enum</code></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"6d=
91b35f-c47b-4b6f-9682-d8ab6ec4e596" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Feature</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>struct</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>union</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>enum</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Memory</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Each member gets its own memory</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>All members share memory</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Each name =3D int constant</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Use</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Store different types together</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Save memory, one value at a time</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Named constants for readability</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Access</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>s.member</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>u.member</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>e.value</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Example</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>struct Student { int id; float marks; };</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>union Data { int i; float f; };</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>enum Week {Sun,Mon,Tue};</code></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>In Short:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Structure</strong> =E2=86=92 Group different types, each has its=
 own memory.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Union</strong> =E2=86=92 Group different types, share memory, sa=
ve space.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Enumeration</strong> =E2=86=92 Named integer constants, improve =
readability.</p></li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p>I can make a <strong>two-column MCQ sheet (15 questions)</strong> for <s=
trong>Structures, Unions, and Enumerations</strong>, just like your previou=
s topics.</p>
<p>Do you want me to do that next?</p>
<ol start=3D"9">
<li>
<p>Input and Output: standard input and output, formatted input and output,=
 file access;</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Perfect =F0=9F=91=8F =E2=80=94 now let=E2=80=99s cover <strong>Input and=
 Output (I/O) in C</strong>, including <strong>standard I/O, formatted I/O,=
 and file access</strong>. This is a <strong>very common topic</strong> in =
Govt IT /  ICT exams. I=E2=80=99ll explain <strong>step by step with exa=
mples</strong>.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A91.StandardInputandOutpu=
t">=F0=9F=A7=A9 <strong>1. Standard Input and Output</strong></h2>
<p>C provides <strong>standard input</strong> and <strong>output streams</s=
trong>:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"d8=
74251d-ae55-409e-ac0b-1c42a05d0f2a" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Stream</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Symbol</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Standard Input</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>stdin</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Keyboard input (<code>scanf()</code>)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Standard Output</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>stdout</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Screen output (<code>printf()</code>)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Standard Error</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>stderr</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Error messages (usually console)</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9a)StandardOutput:printf=
()">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>a) Standard Output: </strong><code>printf()</code>=
</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Prints data to the screen</p></li>
<li>
<p>Can format text using <strong>format specifiers</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"23=
60923a-1b13-412e-abba-00b3457285bb" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Specifier</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Data Type</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>%d</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>int</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>printf("%d", 10);</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>%f</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>float</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>printf("%.2f", 3.1415);</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>%c</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>char</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>printf("%c", 'A');</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>%s</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>string</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>printf("%s", "Hello");</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>%u</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>unsigned int</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>printf("%u", 100);</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>%x</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>hexadecimal</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>printf("%x", 255);</code></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int main() {
    int a =3D 10;
    float b =3D 3.14;
    char c =3D 'R';
    printf("Int: %d, Float: %.2f, Char: %c\n", a, b, c);
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Int: 10=
, Float: 3.14, Char: R
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9b)StandardInput:scanf()=
">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>b) Standard Input: </strong><code>scanf()</code></h3=
>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Reads input from keyboard</p></li>
<li>
<p>Format specifier <strong>must match variable type</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int main() {
    int age;
    char name[20];

    printf("Enter your name: ");
    scanf("%s", name);

    printf("Enter your age: ");
    scanf("%d", &amp;age);

    printf("Name: %s, Age: %d\n", name, age);
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9A=A0=EF=B8=8F <strong>Note:</strong> <code>scanf("%s", name)</code>=
 stops at the first space. Use <code>fgets()</code> for strings with spaces=
.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A92.FormattedInputandOutp=
ut">=F0=9F=A7=A9 <strong>2. Formatted Input and Output</strong></h2>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9FormattedOutput(printf)=
">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>Formatted Output (</strong><code>printf</code><stron=
g>)</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Control width, precision, alignment</p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">printf(=
"%10d", 50);   // prints 50 in a field width of 10
printf("%.2f", 3.14159); // prints 3.14
printf("%-10s", "Hi"); // left-align in width 10
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9FormattedInput(scanf)">=
=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>Formatted Input (</strong><code>scanf</code><strong>)<=
/strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Read specific types of data</p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">scanf("=
%d %f %c", &amp;a, &amp;b, &amp;c);
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Can read multiple inputs in a single line</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A93.FileAccessinC">=F0=9F=
=A7=A9 <strong>3. File Access in C</strong></h2>
<p>C allows <strong>reading from and writing to files</strong> using the <c=
ode>FILE</code><strong> structure</strong> and functions like <code>fopen()=
</code>, <code>fclose()</code>, <code>fprintf()</code>, <code>fscanf()</cod=
e>, <code>fread()</code>, <code>fwrite()</code>.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9a)FileOpening">=F0=9F=
=94=B9 <strong>a) File Opening</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">FILE *f=
p;
fp =3D fopen("data.txt", "r"); // "r" =3D read, "w" =3D write, "a" =3D appe=
nd
if(fp =3D=3D NULL) {
    printf("File not found!\n");
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9b)WritingtoaFile">=F0=
=9F=94=B9 <strong>b) Writing to a File</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">FILE *f=
p =3D fopen("output.txt", "w"); // write mode
fprintf(fp, "Hello World!\n");
fclose(fp);  // Always close file
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9c)ReadingfromaFile">=F0=
=9F=94=B9 <strong>c) Reading from a File</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">FILE *f=
p =3D fopen("input.txt", "r");
char str[100];

while(fgets(str, 100, fp) !=3D NULL) {
    printf("%s", str);
}

fclose(fp);
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9d)FileModes">=F0=9F=94=
=B9 <strong>d) File Modes</strong></h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"e4=
6428c7-b3ba-4c34-b56f-5534e6998217" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Mode</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Meaning</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>"r"</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Open file for reading</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>"w"</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Open file for writing (overwrite)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>"a"</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Append to file</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>"r+"</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Read &amp; write</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>"w+"</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Write &amp; read (overwrite)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>"a+"</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Append &amp; read</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9e)Example:FullFileI/O">=
=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>e) Example: Full File I/O</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int main() {
    FILE *fp;
    fp =3D fopen("data.txt", "w");
    fprintf(fp, "C Programming\n");
    fclose(fp);

    fp =3D fopen("data.txt", "r");
    char str[50];
    while(fgets(str, 50, fp) !=3D NULL) {
        printf("%s", str);
    }
    fclose(fp);

    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output (on screen):</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">C Progr=
amming
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A0KeyPointstoRemember">=
=F0=9F=A7=A0 <strong>Key Points to Remember</strong></h2>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Always check</strong> if file opened successfully (<code>fp !=3D=
 NULL</code>)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Use <code>fclose()</code> to release resources</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>fprintf</code><strong> / </strong><code>fscanf</code> =E2=86=92 fo=
rmatted file I/O</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>fgets</code><strong> / </strong><code>fputs</code> =E2=86=92 strin=
g-based file I/O</p></li>
<li>
<p>Standard I/O (<code>printf</code>, <code>scanf</code>) =E2=86=92 works w=
ith console</p></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=93=9ASummaryTable.1">=F0=9F=
=93=9A <strong>Summary Table</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"ef=
4c2336-9959-4358-987a-71dd64da162c" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Concept</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Function / Example</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Std Output</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>printf("%d", x);</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Print to screen</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Std Input</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>scanf("%d", &amp;x);</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Read from keyboard</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Formatted Output</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>printf("%10d", x);</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Width &amp; precision control</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>File Write</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>fprintf(fp, "text");</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Write formatted data to file</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>File Read</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>fgets(str, size, fp);</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Read line from file</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>File Open</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>fopen("file","r/w/a");</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Open file in mode</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>File Close</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>fclose(fp);</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Close file to save resources</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>In Short:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Standard I/O</strong> =E2=86=92 keyboard &amp; screen</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Formatted I/O</strong> =E2=86=92 control how input/output looks<=
/p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>File I/O</strong> =E2=86=92 read/write data from/to files using =
<code>FILE*</code> and related functions</p></li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<ol start=3D"10">
<li>
<p>Variable length argument list;</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Perfect =F0=9F=91=8F =E2=80=94 now let=E2=80=99s cover <strong>Variable =
Length Argument Lists (variadic functions)</strong> in C. This is a slightl=
y advanced topic, but very useful for <strong>Govt IT /  ICT exams</stro=
ng> and practical programming.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A9WhatisaVariableLengthAr=
gumentList?">=F0=9F=A7=A9 <strong>What is a Variable Length Argument List?<=
/strong></h2>
<p>A <strong>variadic function</strong> is a function that can accept <stro=
ng>a variable number of arguments</strong>.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Normally, C functions have a <strong>fixed number of parameters</strong>=
, but variadic functions allow <strong>flexibility</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Classic example: <code>printf()</code> =E2=80=94 it can take many argume=
nts depending on the format string.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=E2=9A=99=EF=B8=8FHowitWorks">=E2=
=9A=99=EF=B8=8F <strong>How it Works</strong></h2>
<p>C provides <code>&lt;stdarg.h&gt;</code> library to handle variable argu=
ments.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9KeyMacrosin<stdarg.h>">=
=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>Key Macros in </strong><code>&lt;stdarg.h&gt;</code></=
h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"74=
a24e22-c2ef-4998-b610-69f760ab0afe" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Macro</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Purpose</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>va_list</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Declare a variable to hold argument list</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>va_start</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Initialize the argument list</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>va_arg</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Access the next argument</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>va_end</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Clean up</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9SyntaxofaVariadicFuncti=
on">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>Syntax of a Variadic Function</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">return_=
type function_name(fixed_parameters, ...) {
    va_list arg;      // declare variable to handle arguments
    va_start(arg, last_fixed_parameter); // initialize

    // access each argument using va_arg
    type value =3D va_arg(arg, type);

    va_end(arg);      // clean up
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>...</code> =E2=86=92 represents <strong>variable arguments</strong=
></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>last_fixed_parameter</code> =E2=86=92 required for <code>va_start<=
/code></p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9Example1:SumofNumbers">=
=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>Example 1: Sum of Numbers</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;
#include &lt;stdarg.h&gt;

int sum(int count, ...) {
    va_list args;
    va_start(args, count);

    int total =3D 0;
    for(int i =3D 0; i &lt; count; i++) {
        total +=3D va_arg(args, int);  // access each int argument
    }

    va_end(args);
    return total;
}

int main() {
    printf("Sum: %d\n", sum(4, 10, 20, 30, 40)); // 4 arguments
    printf("Sum: %d\n", sum(2, 5, 15));         // 2 arguments
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Sum: 10=
0
Sum: 20
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9Example2:SimplePrintFun=
ction">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>Example 2: Simple Print Function</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;
#include &lt;stdarg.h&gt;

void printNumbers(int n, ...) {
    va_list args;
    va_start(args, n);

    for(int i =3D 0; i &lt; n; i++) {
        printf("%d ", va_arg(args, int));
    }

    va_end(args);
    printf("\n");
}

int main() {
    printNumbers(3, 10, 20, 30);
    printNumbers(5, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5);
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">10 20 3=
0
1 2 3 4 5
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A0ImportantNotes">=F0=9F=
=A7=A0 <strong>Important Notes</strong></h2>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>At least one fixed argument</strong> is recommended to know how =
many variable arguments exist (e.g., <code>count</code> in <code>sum()</cod=
e> example).</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Type safety is not enforced</strong> =E2=80=94 you must know the=
 correct type when using <code>va_arg</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Always call </strong><code>va_end()</code> to clean up.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Variadic functions are <strong>less safe</strong> than fixed-parameter f=
unctions because of type and argument count issues.</p></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9KeyPointsTable">=F0=9F=
=94=B9 <strong>Key Points Table</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"42=
9a5bbc-b93b-4407-8708-65bd899eff07" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Concept</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Notes</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Header file</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>&lt;stdarg.h&gt;</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Needed for variadic functions</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Declare list</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>va_list args;</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Holds argument list</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Initialize</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>va_start(args, last_fixed_arg);</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Must specify last fixed argument</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Access arg</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>va_arg(args, type)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Returns next argument of given type</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Clean up</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>va_end(args)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Free resources</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Example function</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>int sum(int count, ...)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Returns sum of variable arguments</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>In Short:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Variadic functions allow you to pass <strong>any number of arguments</st=
rong> to a function. They are <strong>flexible but unsafe</strong> unless h=
andled carefully. <code>printf()</code> is the most famous example.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p></p>
<ol start=3D"11">
<li>
<p>Command line parameters;</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Perfect =F0=9F=91=8F =E2=80=94 now let=E2=80=99s cover <strong>Command L=
ine Parameters (Arguments)</strong> in C. This is an <strong>important topi=
c</strong> for exams and practical programming. I=E2=80=99ll explain it <st=
rong>clearly, step by step</strong>, with examples.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A9WhatareCommandLineParam=
eters?">=F0=9F=A7=A9 <strong>What are Command Line Parameters?</strong></h2=
>
<p>=F0=9F=91=89 <strong>Command line parameters</strong> are values passed =
to a program <strong>when it is executed from the terminal or command promp=
t</strong>.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Allows the program to <strong>receive input without using </strong><code=
>scanf()</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Useful for programs that need <strong>dynamic input</strong>, like filen=
ames or numbers.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9HowtoReceiveCommandLine=
Arguments">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>How to Receive Command Line Arguments</stro=
ng></h2>
<p>In C, the <code>main()</code><strong> function</strong> can be written a=
s:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int mai=
n(int argc, char *argv[])
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>or</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int mai=
n(int argc, char **argv)
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Explanation:">Explanation:</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"e0=
a672fc-0493-4971-a480-191c1f8c875c" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Parameter</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Meaning</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>argc</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Argument Count =E2=80=94 total number of command line arguments (includi=
ng program name)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>argv</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Argument Vector =E2=80=94 array of strings containing arguments</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9Example:PrintCommandLin=
eArguments">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>Example: Print Command Line Arguments</str=
ong></h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int main(int argc, char *argv[]) {
    printf("Number of arguments: %d\n", argc);
    for(int i =3D 0; i &lt; argc; i++) {
        printf("Argument %d: %s\n", i, argv[i]);
    }
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Example execution in terminal:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">./progr=
am Hello 123
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Output:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Number =
of arguments: 3
Argument 0: ./program
Argument 1: Hello
Argument 2: 123
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 Note:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>argv[0]</code> is <strong>always the program name</strong>.</p></l=
i>
<li>
<p>Remaining elements are the arguments.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9Example:SumofNumbersUsi=
ngCommandLine">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>Example: Sum of Numbers Using Command L=
ine</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;
#include &lt;stdlib.h&gt;

int main(int argc, char *argv[]) {
    int sum =3D 0;

    for(int i =3D 1; i &lt; argc; i++) {
        sum +=3D atoi(argv[i]);  // convert string to integer
    }

    printf("Sum: %d\n", sum);
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Execution:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">./sum 1=
0 20 30
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Output:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Sum: 60
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 <code>atoi()</code> converts <strong>string to integer</str=
ong>.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9PointstoRemember">=F0=
=9F=94=B9 <strong>Points to Remember</strong></h2>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>argc</strong> =E2=89=A5 1 always, because program name is counte=
d.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>argv</strong> is an array of strings (char pointers).</p></li>
<li>
<p>Convert string arguments to numeric types using:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>atoi()</code> =E2=86=92 integer</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>atof()</code> =E2=86=92 float/double</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Command line arguments allow <strong>non-interactive input</strong>, use=
ful for scripts and automation.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Maximum number of arguments depends on the system.</p></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9Example:CheckFileNamefr=
omCommandLine">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>Example: Check File Name from Command L=
ine</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int main(int argc, char *argv[]) {
    if(argc &lt; 2) {
        printf("Usage: %s filename\n", argv[0]);
        return 1;
    }

    printf("File to open: %s\n", argv[1]);
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Execution:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">./progr=
am data.txt
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Output:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">File to=
 open: data.txt
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9QuickSummaryTable.1">=
=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>Quick Summary Table</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"3f=
acfe67-ec90-44b3-8f36-e76fcf128c89" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Concept</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Notes</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>argc</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>int argc</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Number of arguments (including program name)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>argv</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>char *argv[]</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Array of strings (arguments)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Convert string =E2=86=92 int</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>atoi(argv[1])</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Converts argument to integer</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Program name</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>argv[0]</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Always first element</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Usage</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>./program arg1 arg2 ...</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Pass multiple inputs</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>In Short:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Command line parameters let a C program <strong>receive input from termi=
nal at runtime</strong>, making programs more flexible and script-friendly.=
</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p></p>
<ol start=3D"12">
<li>
<p>Error Handling;</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Perfect =F0=9F=91=8F =E2=80=94 now let=E2=80=99s cover <strong>Error Han=
dling in C</strong>. This is a fundamental topic for <strong>Govt IT /  =
ICT exams</strong>, especially when working with <strong>file I/O, memory a=
llocation, or system calls</strong>. I=E2=80=99ll explain it <strong>clearl=
y, step by step</strong>.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A9WhatisErrorHandling?">=
=F0=9F=A7=A9 <strong>What is Error Handling?</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Error handling</strong> is the process of <strong>detecting and =
responding to errors</strong> in a program to prevent <strong>crashes or in=
correct results</strong>.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>In C, <strong>errors can occur</strong> due to:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Invalid user input</p></li>
<li>
<p>File not found</p></li>
<li>
<p>Division by zero</p></li>
<li>
<p>Memory allocation failure</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B91.ErrorHandlinginStanda=
rdI/O">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>1. Error Handling in Standard I/O</strong></h2>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-a)CheckingFileOpening">a) Checking =
File Opening</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int main() {
    FILE *fp =3D fopen("data.txt", "r");
    if(fp =3D=3D NULL) {
        printf("Error: File not found!\n");
        return 1;  // exit program with error
    }
    printf("File opened successfully.\n");
    fclose(fp);
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 Always check if <code>fopen()</code><strong> returns NULL</=
strong> before reading or writing a file.</p>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-b)CheckingUserInput">b) Checking Us=
er Input</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int main() {
    int num;
    printf("Enter an integer: ");
    if(scanf("%d", &amp;num) !=3D 1) {
        printf("Error: Invalid input!\n");
        return 1;
    }
    printf("You entered %d\n", num);
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 <code>scanf()</code> returns the <strong>number of successf=
ully read items</strong> =E2=80=94 check it to catch invalid input.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B92.ErrorHandlingwitherrn=
o">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>2. Error Handling with </strong><code>errno</code><=
/h2>
<p>C provides <code>errno</code> in <code>&lt;errno.h&gt;</code> to identif=
y <strong>system-level errors</strong>.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;
#include &lt;errno.h&gt;
#include &lt;string.h&gt;

int main() {
    FILE *fp =3D fopen("nofile.txt", "r");
    if(fp =3D=3D NULL) {
        printf("Error opening file: %s\n", strerror(errno));
    }
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>errno</code> =E2=86=92 global variable set by system/library funct=
ions</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>strerror(errno)</code> =E2=86=92 human-readable error message</p><=
/li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B93.ExitStatusofaProgram"=
>=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>3. Exit Status of a Program</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>C programs can return an <strong>exit status</strong> using <code>return=
</code> in <code>main()</code> or <code>exit()</code> from <code>&lt;stdlib=
.h&gt;</code>.</p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"08=
4fb7c7-8f48-43c7-82a4-6c47a059dd4e" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Status</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Meaning</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>0</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Success</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Non-zero</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Error occurred</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Example:.9">Example:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdlib.h&gt;
#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int main() {
    printf("Exiting with error code 1\n");
    exit(1);
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B94.HandlingDivisionbyZer=
o">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>4. Handling Division by Zero</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int main() {
    int a =3D 10, b =3D 0;

    if(b =3D=3D 0) {
        printf("Error: Division by zero!\n");
        return 1;
    }

    printf("Result =3D %d\n", a / b);
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 Always <strong>check for illegal operations</strong> before=
 performing them.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B95.Usingassert()forDebug=
ging">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>5. Using </strong><code>assert()</code><strong> =
for Debugging</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>assert()</code> from <code>&lt;assert.h&gt;</code> can <strong>ter=
minate program if a condition is false</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;
#include &lt;assert.h&gt;

int main() {
    int x =3D -5;
    assert(x &gt;=3D 0); // program stops if x &lt; 0
    printf("x =3D %d\n", x);
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Helpful for <strong>debugging and detecting logic errors</strong> during=
 development.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B96.SummaryTableofErrorHa=
ndlingTechniques">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>6. Summary Table of Error Handling T=
echniques</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"c0=
e0e413-bb93-400b-bdab-1e20f6ea23d2" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Technique</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Function / Concept</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Example</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>File Error Check</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>fopen()</code>, check NULL</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>if(fp=3D=3DNULL)</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Input Validation</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>scanf()</code> return</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>if(scanf("%d",&amp;x)!=3D1)</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>System Errors</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>errno</code>, <code>strerror(errno)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>FILE *fp=3Dfopen("nofile","r");</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Program Exit Status</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>exit()</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>exit(1)</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Logic Assertion</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>assert()</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>assert(x&gt;=3D0)</code></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>In Short:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Error handling in C involves <strong>checking return values</strong>, <s=
trong>validating inputs</strong>, using <code>errno</code>, and <strong>ass=
ertions</strong> to prevent crashes and undefined behavior. Proper error ha=
ndling is <strong>essential for reliable programs</strong>, especially in f=
ile operations and user input scenarios.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p></p>
<ol start=3D"13">
<li>
<p>Graphics;</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Perfect =F0=9F=91=8F =E2=80=94 now let=E2=80=99s cover <strong>Graphics =
in C</strong>. While graphics is less common in standard exams, it sometime=
s appears in <strong>Govt IT /  ICT practicals</strong> or programming q=
uestions. I=E2=80=99ll explain <strong>step by step</strong>.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A9WhatisGraphicsinC?">=F0=
=9F=A7=A9 <strong>What is Graphics in C?</strong></h2>
<p>Graphics in C is about <strong>drawing images, shapes, and text</strong>=
 on the screen using functions provided by graphics libraries.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>C <strong>itself does not have built-in graphics</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>We usually use libraries like:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>graphics.h</code> (Turbo C / Borland C)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Modern alternatives: SDL, OpenGL, or Windows API</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B91.BasicConcepts">=F0=9F=
=94=B9 <strong>1. Basic Concepts</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Graphics programs</strong> usually follow these steps:</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Initialize graphics mode</strong></p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Draw graphics objects</strong> (line, circle, rectangle, text)</=
p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Wait for user input or delay</strong></p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Close graphics mode</strong></p></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B92.Usinggraphics.h(Turbo=
Cstyle)">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>2. Using </strong><code>graphics.h</code><str=
ong> (Turbo C style)</strong></h3>
<p><strong>Header file:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;graphics.h&gt;
#include &lt;conio.h&gt;
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-a)InitializeGraphics">a) Initialize=
 Graphics</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int gd =
=3D DETECT, gm;
initgraph(&amp;gd, &amp;gm, "C:\\Turboc3\\BGI");
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>gd</code> =E2=86=92 Graphics driver</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>gm</code> =E2=86=92 Graphics mode</p></li>
<li>
<p>Third parameter =E2=86=92 path to BGI driver (Turbo C only)</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-b)DrawShapes">b) Draw Shapes</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"2a=
a8ae62-8fee-4ea9-a4db-f6103f307d1a" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Function</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>line(x1, y1, x2, y2)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Draw line from (x1,y1) to (x2,y2)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>circle(x, y, r)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Draw circle at (x,y) with radius r</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>rectangle(x1, y1, x2, y2)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Draw rectangle</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>outtextxy(x, y, "text")</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Display text at (x,y)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>setcolor(color)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Set color of shape</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-Example:.10">Example:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;graphics.h&gt;
#include &lt;conio.h&gt;

int main() {
    int gd =3D DETECT, gm;
    initgraph(&amp;gd, &amp;gm, "");

    setcolor(RED);
    rectangle(100, 100, 200, 200);

    setcolor(BLUE);
    circle(150, 150, 50);

    outtextxy(120, 220, "Graphics Example");

    getch();
    closegraph();
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>A red rectangle</p></li>
<li>
<p>A blue circle inside it</p></li>
<li>
<p>Text below shapes</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-c)CloseGraphics">c) Close Graphics<=
/h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">closegr=
aph();
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Releases graphics memory</p></li>
<li>
<p>Restores normal text mode</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
