<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B94.ModernGraphicsinC">=
=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>4. Modern Graphics in C</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Turbo C graphics is <strong>old</strong> and runs in DOS only</p></li>
<li>
<p>Modern alternatives:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>SDL</strong> =E2=86=92 Game &amp; graphics development</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>OpenGL</strong> =E2=86=92 2D/3D graphics</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Windows API</strong> =E2=86=92 GUI applications</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Qt / GTK</strong> =E2=86=92 Advanced graphics &amp; GUI</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B95.SummaryTable">=F0=9F=
=94=B9 <strong>5. Summary Table</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"7d=
75cd14-be56-4864-a48e-46d3c638e495" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Concept</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Function / Example</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Initialize graphics</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>initgraph(&amp;gd, &amp;gm, "path")</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Start graphics mode</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Draw line</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>line(x1,y1,x2,y2)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Draws line</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Draw circle</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>circle(x,y,r)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Draws circle</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Draw rectangle</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>rectangle(x1,y1,x2,y2)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Draw rectangle</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Display text</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>outtextxy(x,y,"text")</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Show text</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Set color</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>setcolor(RED)</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Set color of shape</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Close graphics</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>closegraph()</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Restore normal mode</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>In Short:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Graphics in C allows you to <strong>draw shapes, text, and images</stron=
g> on the screen.<br><code>graphics.h</code> is the classic library (Turbo =
C), while <strong>modern libraries like SDL, OpenGL, or Qt</strong> are use=
d today for real-world applications.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p></p>
<ol start=3D"14">
<li>
<p>Linking;</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Perfect =F0=9F=91=8F =E2=80=94 now let=E2=80=99s cover <strong>Linking i=
n C</strong>. This is an important topic for <strong>Govt IT /  ICT exam=
s</strong>, especially when dealing with <strong>program compilation and mu=
ltiple files</strong>. I=E2=80=99ll explain <strong>step by step</strong>.<=
/p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A9WhatisLinking?">=F0=9F=
=A7=A9 <strong>What is Linking?</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Linking</strong> is the process of <strong>combining object file=
s and libraries</strong> to create a <strong>single executable program</str=
ong>.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>After writing and compiling C code, the compiler produces <strong>object=
 files (</strong><code>.obj</code><strong> or </strong><code>.o</code><stro=
ng>)</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The <strong>linker</strong> combines these object files and resolves ref=
erences to produce the <strong>final executable (</strong><code>.exe</code>=
<strong> or a.out`)</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9TypesofLinkinginC">=F0=
=9F=94=B9 <strong>Types of Linking in C</strong></h2>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Static Linking</strong></p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Dynamic Linking (Shared Libraries)</strong></p></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B91.StaticLinking">=F0=9F=
=94=B9 <strong>1. Static Linking</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>All required code from <strong>libraries</strong> is copied into the <st=
rong>final executable</strong> during compile-time.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Resulting executable is <strong>larger</strong> but <strong>independent =
of external libraries at runtime</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">// main=
.c
#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;
#include "mathlib.h"

int main() {
    printf("Sum: %d\n", add(10, 20));
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Suppose <code>add()</code> is defined in <code>mathlib.c</code>.</p></li=
>
</ul>
<p><strong>Steps to compile:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">gcc -c =
main.c      # produces main.o
gcc -c mathlib.c   # produces mathlib.o
gcc main.o mathlib.o -o program   # linker combines both
./program
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>-c</code> =E2=86=92 compile only (produces object file)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Linking happens in the last step to produce executable</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B92.DynamicLinking(Shared=
Libraries)">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>2. Dynamic Linking (Shared Libraries)</str=
ong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Code is <strong>not copied</strong> into executable. Instead, it <strong=
>links at runtime</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Produces <strong>smaller executable</strong> but requires <strong>librar=
y present at runtime</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Example (Linux):</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">gcc mai=
n.c -lm    # links with math library dynamically
./a.out
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>-lm</code> =E2=86=92 links with math library (<code>libm.so</code>=
) at runtime</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B93.StepsinCompilation&am=
p;Linking">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>3. Steps in Compilation &amp; Linking</stro=
ng></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"3d=
5701be-2c3e-4bbb-bee0-c85132c6ba76" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Step</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Preprocessing</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Handles <code>#include</code>, <code>#define</code>, macros =E2=86=92 pr=
oduces <code>.i</code> file</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Compilation</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Converts <code>.i</code> file to assembly =E2=86=92 <code>.s</code> file=
</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Assembly</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Converts <code>.s</code> to object code =E2=86=92 <code>.o</code> file</=
p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Linking</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Combines object files &amp; libraries =E2=86=92 executable (<code>.exe</=
code>)</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Flow:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Source =
Code =E2=86=92 Preprocessor =E2=86=92 Compiler =E2=86=92 Assembler =E2=86=
=92 Linker =E2=86=92 Executable
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h3 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B94.ExampleofLinkingMulti=
pleFiles">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>4. Example of Linking Multiple Files</strong=
></h3>
<p><strong>File1: add.c</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">int add=
(int a, int b) {
    return a + b;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>File2: main.c</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int add(int, int); // function prototype

int main() {
    printf("Sum: %d\n", add(5, 10));
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Compile &amp; Link:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">gcc mai=
n.c add.c -o program
./program
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Sum: 15
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Both <code>.c</code> files are compiled and linked to form the final pro=
gram.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B95.LinkinginPractice">=
=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>5. Linking in Practice</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Header files (</strong><code>.h</code><strong>)</strong> =E2=86=
=92 tell compiler <strong>what functions exist</strong></p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Source files (</strong><code>.c</code><strong>)</strong> =E2=86=
=92 contain <strong>actual implementation</strong></p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Linker</strong> resolves <strong>references between files</stron=
g></p></li>
<li>
<p>If linker <strong>cannot find a function</strong>, it gives <strong>=E2=
=80=9Cundefined reference=E2=80=9D</strong> error.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B9QuickSummaryTable.2">=
=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>Quick Summary Table</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"d0=
510004-835a-4c44-b2b1-c7829d71a2dd" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Concept</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Linking</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Combining object files and libraries to create executable</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Static Linking</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Libraries copied into executable, bigger size, independent</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Dynamic Linking</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Libraries linked at runtime, smaller executable, requires library presen=
t</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Header Files</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Provide function declarations to compiler</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Object Files</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Compiled <code>.o</code> files ready for linking</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Compilation Flow</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Preprocessing =E2=86=92 Compilation =E2=86=92 Assembly =E2=86=92 Linking=
 =E2=86=92 Executable</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>In Short:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Linking</strong> is the process of <strong>connecting compiled c=
ode and libraries</strong> to make a complete program.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Static linking</strong> =E2=86=92 compile-time, bigger executabl=
e</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Dynamic linking</strong> =E2=86=92 runtime, smaller executable</=
p></li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<p></p>
<ol start=3D"15">
<li>
<p>Library functions</p></li>
</ol>
<p></p>
<p>Perfect =F0=9F=91=8F =E2=80=94 now let=E2=80=99s cover <strong>Library F=
unctions in C</strong>. This is an <strong>important topic</strong> for Gov=
t IT /  ICT exams because <strong>many programs rely on built-in functio=
ns</strong>. I=E2=80=99ll explain <strong>step by step with examples</stron=
g>.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=A7=A9WhatareLibraryFunctions=
?">=F0=9F=A7=A9 <strong>What are Library Functions?</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Library functions</strong> are <strong>predefined functions</str=
ong> in C that you can use <strong>directly</strong> without writing their =
code.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>They are <strong>stored in standard libraries</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>They save time and reduce errors.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Examples: <code>printf()</code>, <code>scanf()</code>, <code>strlen()</c=
ode>, <code>sqrt()</code>, etc.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B91.CategoriesofLibraryFu=
nctions">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>1. Categories of Library Functions</strong></=
h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"7a=
50346f-9570-4f28-a615-1dc9cb04aed2" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Category</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Header File</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Examples</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Input/Output</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>&lt;stdio.h&gt;</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>printf()</code>, <code>scanf()</code>, <code>fprintf()</code>, <co=
de>fscanf()</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>String Handling</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>&lt;string.h&gt;</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>strlen()</code>, <code>strcpy()</code>, <code>strcmp()</code>, <co=
de>strcat()</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Mathematics</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>&lt;math.h&gt;</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>sqrt()</code>, <code>pow()</code>, <code>sin()</code>, <code>cos()=
</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Character Handling</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>&lt;ctype.h&gt;</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>isalpha()</code>, <code>isdigit()</code>, <code>toupper()</code>, =
<code>tolower()</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Time Functions</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>&lt;time.h&gt;</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>time()</code>, <code>clock()</code>, <code>difftime()</code></p></=
td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Memory Management</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>&lt;stdlib.h&gt;</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>malloc()</code>, <code>free()</code>, <code>calloc()</code>, <code=
>realloc()</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Miscellaneous</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>&lt;stdlib.h&gt;</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>exit()</code>, <code>system()</code>, <code>rand()</code>, <code>a=
bs()</code></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B92.Example:StringFunctio=
ns">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>2. Example: String Functions</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;
#include &lt;string.h&gt;

int main() {
    char str1[20] =3D "Hello";
    char str2[20];

    strcpy(str2, str1);   // Copy str1 into str2
    printf("Copied string: %s\n", str2);

    printf("Length of str1: %lu\n", strlen(str1));

    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Copied =
string: Hello
Length of str1: 5
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B93.Example:MathFunctions=
">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>3. Example: Math Functions</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;
#include &lt;math.h&gt;

int main() {
    double x =3D 9.0;
    double y =3D 2.0;

    printf("Square root of %.1f: %.2f\n", x, sqrt(x));
    printf("%.1f raised to %.1f: %.2f\n", x, y, pow(x, y));

    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Square =
root of 9.0: 3.00
9.0 raised to 2.0: 81.00
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=F0=9F=92=A1 <strong>Note:</strong> Use <code>-lm</code> when compiling =
math functions in GCC:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">gcc pro=
gram.c -o program -lm
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B94.Example:CharacterFunc=
tions">=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>4. Example: Character Functions</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">#includ=
e &lt;stdio.h&gt;
#include &lt;ctype.h&gt;

int main() {
    char c =3D 'a';
    if(isalpha(c)) {
        printf("%c is a letter\n", c);
    }

    printf("Uppercase: %c\n", toupper(c));
    return 0;
}
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>=E2=9C=85 Output:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">a is a =
letter
Uppercase: A
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B95.KeyPoints">=F0=9F=94=
=B9 <strong>5. Key Points</strong></h2>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Library functions are precompiled</strong> =E2=80=94 no need to =
write code.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Always <strong>include the correct header file</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Can be used for <strong>input/output, math, string manipulation, memory =
management, etc.</strong></p></li>
<li>
<p>Saves <strong>time and reduces errors</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Some require <strong>linking with libraries</strong> (like <code>-lm</co=
de> for math functions).</p></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Structuredprogramminglanguage-=F0=9F=94=B96.QuickSummaryTable">=
=F0=9F=94=B9 <strong>6. Quick Summary Table</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"51=
4fa41e-9e50-445b-83f5-57fb303d424a" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Header File</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Functions</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Use</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>&lt;stdio.h&gt;</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>printf(), scanf()</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Input/output</p></td>
</tr>
